==English==
===Noun phrase===
'''[[anti]]-[[roll]] [[bar]]'''is a bar that is stressed to reduce [[roll]] (leaning to one side) in a car body during cornering.  They are more likely to be front mounted, but there can be both front and rear, and they take the form of a semi rigid short 'U' shaped bar with each end of the 'U' attached to the suspension at either side.  Downward movement at one side would cause the bar to rotate pivoted at the bottom of the 'U' and cause the opposing side to attempt to follow the movement of the other side.  The purpose of this is to improve handling by discouraging a single wheel from lifting.

This description is simplistic, as there are many different arrangements for anti roll bars, which are not to be confused with [[roll over bars]].

